  "text": "The most important simplification in our case is the fact that, since we are in odd dimensions, the contributions coming from the Seeley-De Witt expansion in (2.7) vanish. Therefore, we only have to take into account the zero mode contribution (2.9). We are then led to the question of which fields lead to discrete zero modes in the background we are considering. Fields with zero modes play of course a crucial rôle in the calculations of [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . There, the background is AdS 2 × S 2 or AdS 2 ×(squashed)S 3 , and the zero modes arise from the \"exceptional\" zero modes of one-forms, metric and gravitinoes on AdS 2 described in [CITATION_6] .",
